sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as React Client
    participant AuthCtrl as Auth Controller
    participant AuthSvc as Auth Service
    participant JwtUtil as JWT Utility
    participant Filter as JWT Auth Filter
    participant StatusCtrl as Protected Endpoint
    
    Note over Client,StatusCtrl: Step 1: Authentication
    
    Client->>AuthCtrl: POST /api/auth/login<br/>{email, password}
    AuthCtrl->>AuthSvc: Validate credentials
    AuthSvc->>JwtUtil: generateToken(userDetails)
    
    Note over JwtUtil: Sign JWT with:<br/>- Username (email)<br/>- Expiration (24hrs)<br/>- Secret key (HS256)
    
    JwtUtil->>AuthSvc: JWT Token String
    AuthSvc->>Client: 200 OK {token: "eyJ..."}
    Client->>Client: localStorage.setItem('syncup_token')
    
    Note over Client,StatusCtrl: Step 2: Using Token
    
    Client->>Client: Prepare next request
    Client->>Client: Read token from localStorage
    Client->>Client: Add header:<br/>Authorization: Bearer eyJ...
    
    Client->>Filter: Request with JWT in header
    
    Note over Filter: JWT Validation
    
    Filter->>JwtUtil: extractUsername(token)
    JwtUtil->>JwtUtil: Parse JWT<br/>Verify signature<br/>Check expiration
    
    alt Token Valid
        JwtUtil->>Filter: username/email
        Filter->>Filter: Load UserDetails
        Filter->>Filter: Set SecurityContext
        Filter->>StatusCtrl: Pass through
        StatusCtrl->>Client: 200 OK {data}
    else Token Invalid/Expired
        JwtUtil->>Filter: Exception
        Filter->>Client: 401 Unauthorized
        Client->>Client: localStorage.removeItem('syncup_token')
        Client->>Client: Redirect to /login
    end
    
    Note over Client,StatusCtrl: Step 3: WebSocket Connection
    
    Client->>Client: Connect to WebSocket
    Client->>Client: Send header:<br/>Authorization: Bearer eyJ...
    
    Note over Filter: WebSocket JWT Validation<br/>Similar to HTTP filter
    
    Filter->>JwtUtil: Validate token
    JwtUtil->>Filter: Valid
    Filter->>StatusCtrl: Allow subscription
    StatusCtrl->>Client: Subscribe to /topic/status
